text: Skillikalia Bayou is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. Skillikalia is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean either (sources vary) "geese come there", "small white beads", or "sparrow-hawk". Variant names are "Skillet Goliah Bayou" and "Skilleteliah Creek". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Warren County, Mississippi
title: Skillikalia Bayou
